    <main>
        <section id="current">
            <h2>Current Trends</h2>
            <p>Virtual Reality (VR) has revolutionized gaming by offering immersive experiences that blur the line between real and virtual worlds.</p>
            <p>Popular VR devices like Oculus Rift, HTC Vive, and PlayStation VR have gained wide acceptance.</p>
            <p>VR games provide realistic simulations, interactive gameplay, and social interaction in virtual environments.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="data">
            <h2>Data Insights</h2>
            <p>Market research indicates a growing demand for VR gaming experiences, with forecasts predicting significant growth.</p>
            <p>Major investments in VR technology by companies like Sony, Facebook (owner of Oculus), and HTC have fueled innovation and improved user experiences.</p>
            <p>VR gaming appeals to a diverse audience, indicating a broad market potential.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="future">
            <h2>Future Prospects</h2>
            <p>The future of VR in gaming holds exciting possibilities, with advancements poised to further revolutionize the industry.</p>
            <p>Technological breakthroughs will enhance immersion, making virtual worlds nearly indistinguishable from reality.</p>
            <p>Integration of AI algorithms will personalize gameplay experiences.</p>
            <p>Example: A VR game analyzing player interactions to offer personalized and educational experiences.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="advantages">
            <h2>Advantages of VR in Gaming</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Immersive experiences enhance engagement and enjoyment.</li>
                <li>Exploration of diverse scenarios not possible in traditional gaming.</li>
                <li>Social interaction and multiplayer experiences.</li>
                <li>Enhanced learning through interactive simulations.</li>
                <li>Health and wellness benefits.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section id="job-fields">
            <h2>Job Fields in Virtual Reality (VR)</h2>
            <p>VR technology offers diverse job opportunities across industries:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>VR Game Developer</li>
                <li>VR UX/UI Designer</li>
                <li>VR Content Creator (3D modeling, animation)</li>
                <li>VR Software Engineer</li>
                <li>VR QA Tester</li>
                <li>VR Project Manager</li>
                <li>VR Educator</li>
                <li>VR Healthcare Specialist</li>
                <li>VR Marketing Specialist</li>
                <li>VR Researcher</li>
            </ul>
            <p>These job fields offer exciting career paths for VR enthusiasts.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="conclusion">
            <h2>Conclusion</h2>
            <p>Virtual Reality in gaming is driving innovation and shaping entertainment's future with immersive experiences and personalized gameplay.</p>
            <p>As VR technology advances, the industry will witness significant growth, catering to diverse preferences and expectations.</p>
        </section>
